-- NFL’s Chicago Bears Name Mike Tice Offensive Coordinator, Replacing Martz
-- B y   J a y   B e b e r m a n
-- 2012-01-06T20:09:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-06/nfl-s-chicago-bears-name-mike-tice-offensive-coordinator-replacing-martz.html
The  Chicago Bears  named Mike Tice
offensive coordinator, replacing Mike Martz, the National
Football League team said in a statement.  Tice, head coach of the  Minnesota Vikings  from 2002-2005,
had been in charge of  Chicago ’s offensive line. The Bears parted
ways with Martz on Jan. 3.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
